MediaPipe Solutions guide
---------------------------

MediaPipe Solutions provides a suite of libraries and tools for you to quickly apply artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) techniques in your applications. You can plug these solutions into your applications immediately, customize them to your needs, and use them across multiple development platforms. MediaPipe Solutions is part of the MediaPipe open source project, so you can further customize the solutions code to meet your application needs



Media Pipe provides many landmarks:
----------------------------------
In MediaPipe, a landmark is a specific key point on an object (like a face, hand, or body) that a machine learning model detects and tracks.

A landmark = an important coordinate point (x, y, z) on a body part.

1)Hand landmark
2)Face landmark
3)Mesh landmark
4)Pose landmark


Hand Landmark
-------------

-Hand landmarks are specific key points detected on a hand by computer vision models to understand the structure, position, and movement of the hand.

-In MediaPipe Hands from MediaPipe, the system detects 21 landmarks on a single hand.

eg: hand detection,sign language,virtual mouse,gestures


Face Landmarks:(Collects only 6 cordinates)
---------------

The MediaPipe Face Detector task lets you detect faces in an image or video. You can use this task to locate faces and facial features within a frame. This task uses a machine learning (ML) model that works with single images or a continuous stream of images. The task outputs face locations, along with the following facial key points: left eye, right eye, nose tip, mouth, left eye tragion, and right eye tragion




Face Mesh landmark(collect all cordinates on a face- 478 landmarks)
------------------

Face Mesh landmarks are many small key points detected on a human face to create a detailed 3D map of the face.     

They are generated by MediaPipe Face Mesh, which is part of MediaPipe.

eg: emotion detection,eye drowsiness detection


